name: Mushroom Burger
descripition: LThis scrumptious burger sits under a chilli lamb pattie, roasted bell pepper dip, onions, tomatoes and lettuce.

name: Perfect Lamb Satay Burger
descripition: Succulent lamb burgers with the crunchiness of cashew nuts and the creaminess of peanut butter smothered with a gorgeous satay sauce.

name: Lamb and Tomato Stuffed Burger
descripition: A perfectly shaped lamb pattie cooked to perfection. The tomatoes aren't just a topping but the spotlight of this beautiful dish.

name: Fish Burger
descripition: If a burger for you is all about the meat and protein then you're at the right place.

name: Chicken Feta Cheese Burger
descripition: Chicken mince marinated with salt, pepper and feta cheese is only the beginning of this ultimate wonder.

name: Lentil and Mushroom Burger
descripition: For the healthy and calorie conscious folks we've got this tasty burger.

name: Stuffed Bean Burger
descripition: Being a vegetarian is no reason to deny yourself the gluttonous pleasures of an overstuffed bun.

name: Lamb Burger
descripition: Lamb it out with this thick and juicy pattie accompanied with a crunchy bitter sweet raddish slaw and chilli aioli.

name: Cheese Pizza
descripition: It should be no shocker that a classic is the statistical favorite. Cheese pizza is one of the most popular choices.

name: Veggie Pizza
descripition: When you want to jazz up your cheese pizza with color and texture, veggies are the perfect topping.

name: Pepperoni Pizza
descripition: There is a reason this is one of the most popular types of pizza.

name: Meat Pizza
descripition: If pepperoni just isn’t enough, and you’re looking for a pie with a bit more heft, a meat pizza is a perfect and popular choice.

name: Margherita Pizza
descripition: Deceptively simple, the Margherita pizza is made with basil, fresh mozzarella, and tomatoes.

name: BBQ Chicken Pizza
descripition: If you love BBQ chicken and you love pizza, why not put them together?

name: Hawaiian Pizza
descripition: Pineapple might not be the first thing that comes to mind when you think pizza.

name: Buffalo Pizza
descripition: Who says your pizza has to be strictly tomato-sauce based? Branch out with some buffalo sauce on your pie.

name: Spaghetti
descripition: Perhaps one of the most popular pasta types in the world, spaghetti consists of long, thin noodles which can be paired with a wide variety of sauces.

name: Penne
descripition: Another popular shape, penne has a round, tube like structure, with diagonal cuts at either end.

name: Lasagne
descripition: Contrary to popular belief, lasagne is the name of the thin sheets of pasta that make up a dish, rather than the dish itself.

name: Ravioli
descripition: Ravioli are pillow shaped squares of dough that can pretty much do anything.

name: Linguine
descripition: Very similar to the likes of spaghetti, linguine is a little flatter and is considered to be more luxurious.

name: Rigatoni
descripition: Much like penne, rigatoni are tubes with small ridges on the outside, but they are slightly wider and cut into a square rather than diagonally.

name: Farfalle
descripition: Known as ‘bow-tie’ pasta and translating to ‘butterfly’ from Italian, this pasta is shaped like exactly that.

name: Fusilli
descripition: This pasta has a spiralled, corkscrew like shape that pair perfectly with rich meat sauces or chunky vegetables as the chunks get caught in the crevices of the twirls giving the dish a lovely texture.

name: Arborio Rice
descripition: Arborio rice is a medium grain rice that is wider in size and has a characteristic white dot at the center of the grain.

name: Basmati Rice
descripition: When cooked, basmati rice grains are long, dry, and separate.

name: Black Rice
descripition: Black rice, also known as forbidden rice, gets its color from anthocyanins, the same antioxidant that's found in blueberries and blackberries.

name: Bomba Rice
descripition: Bomba rice is a medium grain rice that is cultivated in the Valencia region of Spain.

name: Brown Rice
descripition: Brown rice is a whole grain that has its bran and germ layers still intact, which gives the rice its characteristic tan color.

name: Jasmine Rice
descripition: Cultivated in Thailand, jasmine rice will bring an exotic flair and flavorful accent to any dish.

name: Grain White Rice
descripition: Long grain white rice is most common rice used in traditional American recipes, and it's also popular in Asian and Mexican cuisine.

name: Parboiled Rice
descripition: Parboiled rice is rice that has been partially boiled in its inedible outer husk.

name: Old Fashioned
descripition: There may be no better test of a bartender's mettle than ordering an Old Fashioned.

name: Margarita
descripition: Cloyingly sweet margarita mixes have given this drink a bad name. A well-made version is a fresh mix of lime juice and tequila.

name: Cosmopolitan
descripition: The cosmo became almost ubiquitous in the '90s thanks to the TV show.

name: Negroni
descripition: A favorite of bartenders all over the world, the Negroni is a simple three-ingredient cocktail.

name: Moscow Mule
descripition: Popular for good reason, the Moscow Mule is one of the most refreshing things to sip on a hot summer day.

name: Martini
descripition: LJames Bond was wrong—whether you drink it with gin or vodka, stirred is the way to go when ordering a martini.

name: Mojito
descripition: Originating in Cuba, this refreshing rum-based sip is filled with mint and lime—a perfect combination for sipping by the pool or beach.

name: Whiskey Sour
descripition: Perhaps the most refreshing whiskey cocktail, this is an old reliable favorite.

name: AFFOGATO
descripition: Espresso poured on a vanilla ice cream. Served in a cappuccino cup.

name: AMERICANO
descripition: Espresso with added hot water (100–150 ml). Often served in a cappuccino cup. (The espresso is added into the hot water rather than all the water being flowed through the coffee that would lead to over extraction.)

name: CAFFÈ LATTE
descripition: A tall, mild 'milk coffee' (about 150-300 ml). An espresso with steamed milk and only a little milk foam poured over it. Serve in a latte glass or a coffee cup. Flavoured syrup can be added.

name: CAFFÈ MOCHA
descripition: A caffè latte with chocolate and whipped cream, made by pouring about 2 cl of chocolate sauce into the glass, followed by an espresso shot and steamed milk.

name: CAFÈ AU LAIT
descripition: French morning coffee. Made by mixing dark roasted filter coffee (often prepared with French Press) and warm milk. Served in a bowl or a large coffee cup.

name: CAPPUCCINO
descripition: A coffee drink consisting of espresso and a milk foam mixture (drink size about 160–240 ml). Served in a cappuccino cup.

name: COLD BREW COFFEE
descripition: Cold Brew Coffee is a smooth, cold beverage prepared by brewing freshly ground coffee in cold water. In the Cold Brew process, time makes up for heat.

name: DOUBLE ESPRESSO
descripition: Double portion of espresso in a cappuccino/espresso cup.
